
@startuml

' Song Class
class Song {
    +title: String
    +year: int
    +length: int
    +genre: String
    +artist: Artist
    +id: String
}

' Artist Class
class Artist {
    +name: String
    +dateOfBirth: Date
    +websiteURL: String
    +id: String
}

' User Class
class User {
    +id: String
    +name: String
    +address: String
    +type: UserType
}

' UserType Enumeration
enum UserType {
    REGULAR,
    BUSINESS
}

' BusinessUser Class (inherits from User)
class BusinessUser {
    +vatNumber: String
}

' RegularUser Class (inherits from User)
class RegularUser {
    +purchaseHistory: List<Purchase>
}

' Purchase Class
class Purchase {
    +item: Song
    +user: User
    +type: PurchaseType
}

' PurchaseType Enumeration
enum PurchaseType {
    SINGLE,
    ALBUM
}

' Album Class
class Album {
    +trackList: List<Hit>
    +suggestedTo: List<RegularUser>
}

' Hit Class
class Hit {
    +trackNumber: int
    +song: Song
    +artist: Artist
}

' Association between Song and Artist
Song "1" -- "1" Artist : belongsTo

' Association between User and BusinessUser / RegularUser
User <|-- BusinessUser
User <|-- RegularUser

' Association between RegularUser and Purchase
RegularUser "1" -- "0..*" Purchase : purchases

' Association between Purchase and Song
Purchase "1" -- "1" Song : includes

' Association between Album and Hit
Album "1" -- "0..*" Hit : contains

' Association between Hit and Song
Hit "1" -- "1" Song : isA

' Association between Hit and Artist
Hit "1" -- "1" Artist : isA

@enduml

---

### ✅ Explanation of Key Relationships:
- **Song** has a **unique relationship** with an **Artist**, since each song belongs to exactly one artist.
- A **User** can be either a **BusinessUser** or a **RegularUser** — this is modeled using inheritance.
- **BusinessUser** can only upload **Singles** (which are individual songs).
- **RegularUser** can buy **Singles** or **Albums** (comprising multiple **Hits**).
- **Hits** are part of **Albums** and are also individual **Songs**.
- **Purchase** tracks what a **RegularUser** buys, and includes a reference to the **Song** or **Album**.
- **Albums** may be suggested to other **RegularUsers** based on behavior.

